Building anything of value often takes 5-10+ years. Ethics are critical as are avoiding product shortcuts that lead to insurmountable technical (or governance) debt.

Sounds like a must-read for every founder and investor. Building a business is a marathon and we all need to take a hard look at the industry that celebrates overnight success instead of grit and being a good fiduciary to your investors, partners and customers.
Elizabeth Holmes is a liar. She didn’t sell a vision, she sold a solution that she couldn’t deliver. Read the Bad Blood book, it was a farce from the beginning. cc: @JohnCarreyrou

There's a clear difference between lie and communicating your vision as a founder. Think real-estate developer showing spectacular renderings at a construction site. Up to the buyer to access the risks of execution and up to the seller to be truthful about what has been built.
